title: Baker gets a prime seat at Governors’ Ball: Next to Ivanka Trump
text:
Google+
Win McNamee/Getty Images/File
President Donald Trump's daughter, Ivanka Trump, at the White House earlier this week.
By Jaclyn Reiss Globe Staff February 27, 2017
Massachusetts Governor Charlie Baker apparently got quite a nice seat at the Governors’ Ball Sunday night: right beside first daughter Ivanka Trump.
View Story Trump toasts nation’s governors ahead of health care talks President Trump welcomed state leaders to a black-tie ball at the White House ahead of discussions about repealing Obamacare.
The state’s leader was in attendance at the black-tie ball at the White House ahead of discussions about President Donald Trump’s plans to repeal and replace the Affordable Care Act, also known as Obamacare.
At the dinner, Trump saluted the nation’s governors, joking that ‘‘it’s such an easy job you have.’’
Related Trump toasts nation’s governors ahead of health care talks
Material from the Associated Press was used in this report.
